{"title":"Trek CHRGtime Recharges All Your Electronics in 1 Customizable Charging Station Organizer","link":"https://bikerumor.com/trek-chrgtime-recharges-all-your-electronics-in-1-customizable-charging-station-organizer/","date":1710257465000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station-800x533.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" alt=\"Trek CHRGtime tidy organized electronic cycling gadget accessory charger charging station\" /></p>\n<p>Lights, GPS, derailleur batteries, even your phone… this new customizable Trek CHRGtime charging station is a one-stop shop for keeping all of your electronic cycling gadgets topped off. And that tangle of wires out of sight. Yes, this is a $125 USB charger. But to any cyclist with a bunch of small electronic gadgets to keep charged, Trek’s new CHRGtime might finally be the solution to managing all those cables. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Trek CHRGtime organized electronic gadget charger</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_open-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_open-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Trek CHRGtime tidy organized electronic cycling gadget accessory charger charging station, open\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_open-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_open-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_open-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_open-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_open-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_open-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_open-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Trek)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This new Trek CHRGtime is a simple plastic box designed to tidy up the modern cyclist’s life a little bit. Open it up and there’s a soft lined tray to keep SRAM AXS battery chargers, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/best-cycling-gps-computers-mtb-road-gravel-review/\" target=\"_blank\">GPS devices</a>, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-best-gps-watches-for-cycling/\" target=\"_blank\">smartwatches</a>, and various other <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/best-bike-lights/\" target=\"_blank\">bike lights</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/other-fun-stuff/gadgets/\" target=\"_blank\">gadgets</a> neatly separated. Then, tucked under that is a 6-port USB charger and a bunch of wires that you can thread out to the appropriate cubby.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_closed.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_closed-800x427.jpg\" alt=\"Trek CHRGtime tidy organized electronic cycling gadget accessory charger charging station, closed\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_closed-800x427.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_closed-297x158.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_closed-120x64.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_closed-768x410.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_closed-1536x819.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_closed.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Close the lid and all the jumble of wires disappears. And a series of 6 LEDs outside tells you charging status for each gadget inside.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_LED-charge-indicators.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_LED-charge-indicators-800x450.jpg\" alt=\"Trek CHRGtime tidy organized electronic cycling gadget accessory charger charging station, LED indicator lights\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_LED-charge-indicators-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_LED-charge-indicators-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_LED-charge-indicators-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_LED-charge-indicators-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_LED-charge-indicators-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_LED-charge-indicators-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_LED-charge-indicators.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech details</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_inside.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"384\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_inside-800x384.jpg\" alt=\"Trek CHRGtime tidy organized electronic cycling gadget accessory charger charging station, open inside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_inside-800x384.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_inside-297x143.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_inside-120x58.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_inside-768x369.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_inside-1536x737.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_inside.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The charger itself has 6 USB ports – 5 classic USB-A and 1 USB-C. Its power supply is rated at 65W max, which likely is to prevent the overheating you can get with a lot of fast-charging. But that’s probably plenty to get the max out of 5 devices at a time, or maybe even more out of the USB-C cable with fewer drained devices at the same time. (In practice, USB-A is limited to 12W per device, while the USB-C can do 20W and more for fast-charging.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The closed box is 316mm long x 190mm wide x 80mm high or 12.4″ x 7.5″ x 3.1″. (<em>Roughly the same size as 2 reams of paper</em>). </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_packed-full-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_packed-full-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Trek CHRGtime tidy organized electronic cycling gadget accessory charger charging station, packed\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_packed-full-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_packed-full-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_packed-full-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_packed-full-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_packed-full-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_packed-full-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_packed-full-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That means the biggest inside cubby is about 9x15cm. That’s big enough for pretty much any GPS. But not quite enough room for a modern smartphone with a charging cable sticking out the bottom of it. The long ones are ~4x18cm to fit one long or two smaller gadgets.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_rear-extra-cable-port.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_rear-extra-cable-port-800x480.jpg\" alt=\"Trek CHRGtime tidy organized electronic cycling gadget accessory charger charging station, extra cable channel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_rear-extra-cable-port-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_rear-extra-cable-port-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_rear-extra-cable-port-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_rear-extra-cable-port-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_rear-extra-cable-port-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_rear-extra-cable-port.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, there’s also a cable port out of the back of the box. So, one wire can charge a phone or bigger device in the shallow recess on top of the charging station. No wireless charging though. But I think you could stick a Qi standard charging pad to the lid’s underside for wireless charging on top. At least, that’s what I would do with this on my desktop.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Trek CHRGtime Charging Station – Pricing &amp; availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_on-table-top-without-a-wire.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_on-table-top-without-a-wire-800x480.jpg\" alt=\"Trek CHRGtime tidy organized electronic cycling gadget accessory charger charging station, closed\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_on-table-top-without-a-wire-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_on-table-top-without-a-wire-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_on-table-top-without-a-wire-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_on-table-top-without-a-wire-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_on-table-top-without-a-wire-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-CHRGtime-tidy-organized-electronic-cycling-gadget-accessory-charger-charging-station_on-table-top-without-a-wire.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Trek CHRGtime Charging Station is only available for the moment in-store at Trek dealers. It will set you back $125 in the US or 100€ in Europe. Who would have thought that a brick-and-mortar bikeshop is where you’d buy the tidiest solution to charge all of your little electronic gadgets.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">TrekBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-chrgtime-recharges-all-your-electronics-in-1-customizable-charging-station-organizer/\">Trek CHRGtime Recharges All Your Electronics in 1 Customizable Charging Station Organizer</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"360a6bdaadabce53e036f26a1a298723f6c43a25b82293e7c3b388d3e6a5dfff","category":"Cycling"}